Automated Refactoring:
    Identify inefficiencies or redundant code and replace them with optimized versions.

Task Expansion:
    Add new modules or features based on user requirements, such as adding a REST API to an existing application.

Error Debugging:
    Automatically diagnose and fix runtime or logical errors in the code.

Performance Optimization:
Analyze bottlenecks (e.g., through cProfile) and propose optimizations.

Extensibility:
    Supports plugins or external libraries for more advanced features.
